# Four-option chooser (Cursor / Composer / Auto)

Substantive replies in this workspace end with **exactly four numbered next moves** (`1.` through `4.`), plain markdown, **mission-ranked**, concrete in the first clause. **Option 4** is the user-authorship slot (`4. Provide your own next move.` or equivalent).

Pure acknowledgments with **no** decision surface may omit the quad; default is four.

Canon: chooser **doctrine** in `CLAUDE.md` **Choosers are control surfaces**; **Skill routing** (end of `CLAUDE.md` / mirrored here) holds the full **IDE agents** clause — that paragraph opens by pointing at **Choosers**, then states plain markdown `1`–`4`.
